# Git-ignored paths symlinked from the main tree into every new worktree.
#
# `git worktree add` materializes only TRACKED files, so a fresh worktree starts
# without any of these — silently. Anything CREATED at one of these paths inside a
# worktree also dies with it on `git worktree remove` (ignored paths are excluded from
# git's dirty check). A symlink prevents both: the worktree shares the main tree's
# copy, and removing the worktree removes only the link.
#
# One path per line. `#` comments and blank lines are ignored. A path that does not
# exist in the main tree is skipped, so listing an optional one costs nothing.

local
.env
.ai-jail

# Per-harness agent config (skills, settings) — git-ignored, needed by every session.
.claude
.codex
.opencode
.gemini
.agents

